summary: An Ordinance appropriating the sum of Three Hundred ($300) dollars out of the general fund of The City of Seattle to pay the claim of Thomas M. Brown and Alice J. Brown for personal injuries received by Alice J. Brown on the 14th day of June, 1916, while alighting from street car at the intersection of Lucille Street and Duwamish Avenue, Seattle, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
